Paper Code: ETCS-407
Paper: Complexity Theory


UNIT I
Complexity, properties common to complex systems, introduction to Net logo, Dynamics and Chaos, Fractals, Information, Order, and Randomness, Maxwell's Demon, Shannon Information.
[T1][R2][T2]

UNIT II
Cellular Automata, Game of life, Cellular Automata as Dynamical Systems, Models of Biological Self- Organization, Ant Foraging and Task Allocation, Information Processing in Biological Systems, Models of Cooperation in Social Systems, The Prisoner's Dilemma.
[T1][R1]

UNIT III
Small-World Networks, Scale-Free and Long-Tailed Degree Distributions, Scaling in Cities, Metabolic Scaling.
[T1][T2][R1]

Unit IV
Evolving Automata, Agent Behavior, Adaptation, Taxonomy of 2 x 2 Games, Game Theory, One Agent, Many Games.
[T2][R1][No. of hrs. 11]


